The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions subject to matroid constraints, which are classic topics in theoretical computer science and optimization. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category. The paper also introduces a new algorithm for adaptive optimization problems, which involves machine learning and decision-making under uncertainty, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the theoretical properties of the algorithm, including approximation guarantees, which could place it in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
